  "intro": "Two prisms wake the vault; the Beam bares its core; then the last stair rises only for the one whose partner holds the ground.",
  "designNotes": "The colossus finale in three staged phases. PHASE 1 (wake): each side chapel holds a prism (a light carryable) guarded by a warden; ferry prismL/prismR across the arena and set each down within docking range of socketL/socketR (kind matches accepts) — a filled socket removes the occluder on that beam so emitter emL->recL and emR->recR light; both receivers lit wakes the arena. PHASE 2 (colossus): 'kol' is a two-role boss (weakTo tractor) — one player exposes its core with the Tractor while the other strikes, until kol.down. PHASE 3 (ascension): climb the ascending walkway to finalPlate, but the floating steps only exist while a partner holds an anchor plate. Role-swap: P1 holds anchorBase so P2 climbs the lower flight to the mid platform; P2 steps onto anchorMid, which keeps the lower flight up AND raises the upper flight; P1 then climbs and continues up to finalPlate while P2 holds anchorMid. solved = kol.down && finalPlate.pressed && recL.lit && recR.lit spans three families: beam-item (receivers/sockets/collectibles) + mass (plates) + combat (colossus).",
  "fog": { "color": "#252043", "density": 0.026 },
